This paper focuses on the use of UAVs for wireless communication in disaster areas, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the optimization problem of maximizing user throughput while maintaining fairness, which is related to robotics (cs.RO) and control (cs.CR). The use of UAVs for disaster relief also involves coordination and decision-making, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the use of wireless communication, which is related to information theory (cs.IT).
